{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-picus-vaillantii", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-picus-vaillantii", "name": "Levaillant's woodpecker", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "bird-levaillant-s-woodpecker-64fd4073", "name": "Levaillant's woodpecker", "englishName": "Levaillant's woodpecker", "latinName": "Picus vaillantii", "type": "bird", "status": "LC", "summary": "Levaillant's woodpecker (Picus vaillantii) or Levaillant's green woodpecker, is a large African member of the woodpecker family Picidae. Taxonomy Levaillant's woodpecker is sometimes considered a subspecies of the European green woodpecker. It is monotypic, meaning it has no subspecies. This species was named in honour of the French explorer, collector and ornithologist, François Le Vaillant. Distribution and habitat Levaillant's woodpecker is found in the three Maghreb countries Morocco, Algeria and Tunisia in northwest Africa. It breeds in mountain forests up to the treeline at around 2000m. Description Levaillant's woodpecker is 30–33 cm in length with a 45–51 cm wingspan. It is very similar to the European green woodpecker and the Iberian Green woodpecker (especially females). Both Levaillant's woodpecker and the Iberian Green woodpecker were formerly considered subspecies of P. viridis. Levaillant's woodpecker is dark green above and yellowish green below, with a crimson nape. The black moustache has a pale border above. The rump is chrome yellow and the outer webs of the primaries are barred black and white. The bill and feet are slate grey. Sexes are similar except that the male has a crimson crown, whereas the female's crown is grey. Like .P. v. sharpei, both sexes lack the black on the lores and around the eye shown by most forms of the green woodpecker. The call is a loud ringing laugh, plue, plue, plue, very like the green woodpecker's yaffle, but perhaps slightly faster. Behaviour This woodpecker's insect food is captured by a rapid outward flick of the long tongue, and gummed to its tip by sticky saliva. Though a large and heavy bird it has an easy, bounding flight. The nest is a hole in a tree, and 4-8 glossy white eggs are laid on wood chips. References", "shortSummary": "Levaillant's woodpecker (Picus vaillantii) or Levaillant's green woodpecker, is a large African member of the woodpecker family Picidae. Ta…", "locations": ["摩洛哥", "阿尔及利亚", "突尼西亞"], "habitats": ["山地森林"], "lat": 32.0, "lng": -6.0, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b1/Levaillant%27s_Woodpecker_-_Oukaimeden_Marocco_07_6526.jpg/960px-Levaillant%27s_Woodpecker_-_Oukaimeden_Marocco_07_6526.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-picus", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-picus-vaillantii", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-picus", "species": "taxonomy-species-picus-vaillantii"}, "expandable": true, "x": -462.59, "y": -134.9, "z": -263.55}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-picus", "name": "Picus", "latinName": "Picus", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Picus（Picus）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联13种鸟类，如Crimson-winged woodpecker、黄冠啄木鸟、鳞腹啄木鸟等13种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 13, "x": 495.16, "y": -235.32, "z": 68.07}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-picus-vaillantii", "name": "Levaillant's woodpecker", "latinName": "Picus vaillantii", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Levaillant's woodpecker（Picus vaillantii）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Levaillant's woodpecker。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": -462.59, "y": -134.9, "z": -260.9}], "links": [{"key": "bird-levaillant-s-woodpecker-64fd4073__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-picus-vaillantii",